    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35c.13"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Coat of Arms</figDesc>
                    </figure> 
                    <hi rend="caps">HASTINGS COLLEGE</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Hastings, Nebraska
                        <lb/>
                    68901
                        <lb/>
                    
                    Student Association Office 
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Nov. 1, 1971</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I cannot begin to tell you how much the students of Hastings College enjoyed your visit to our campus. You left with so many of us a great sense of joy and happiness about life in this state and in this world. You renewed our hope for a better world and our willingness to make this a better place for all of us to live. We hope that you left Hastings College knowing you have many new friends and we pray that you will return.</p>
                
                <p>Personally, I cannot think of a greater honor then to have served as your host on our campus. You can never know the great effect you had on me as a human being. Enclosed in this letter are the articles from the Hastings Tribune and the article I wrote about you for the school paper. My comments are those of private observations I made and noted while being with you; they can never adequately describe all the feelings I have for you. You are much bigger and more pwoerful than words can express!</p> 
                
                <p>Annie, the young women who was with me, and I would like to extend our love and deepest respect and best wishes for future success and long life. <hi rend="underline">Grandfather</hi>, our prayers go with you always and I hope that I will have the opportunity to meet with you and write another article about you. May the love and peace of God be with you always.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>With greatest affection,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Bill Tacey</signed> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
